question:
District category contains Preservation District, and High-rise Apartment Complex.
Supermarkets category contains Grocery Outlet, and H-E-B.
Product category contains Pies, and Coffee.
Ingredient category contains Grits, and Sugar.
The number of each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Grocery Outlet equals 7 times the sum of each Grocery Outlet 's Ingredient and each Pies 's Ingredient.
The number of each Preservation District 's Grocery Outlet equals 10 more than each H-E-B 's Pies.
The number of each H-E-B 's Coffee equals the sum of each Pies 's Sugar, each Grocery Outlet 's Product, each Preservation District 's Supermarkets, and each Coffee 's Sugar.
The number of each H-E-B 's Pies equals each Coffee 's Sugar.
The number of each High-rise Apartment Complex 's H-E-B equals 14 times the difference of each H-E-B 's Pies and each Coffee 's Sugar.
The number of each Coffee 's Grits equals 4 more than the difference of each H-E-B 's Pies and each Coffee 's Sugar.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Pies equals 8 more than the sum of each Pies 's Sugar and each Pies 's Ingredient.
The number of each Pies 's Sugar equals 17 more than each Pies 's Grits.
The number of each Coffee 's Sugar equals 3.
The number of each Preservation District 's H-E-B equals each Pies 's Sugar.
The number of each Pies 's Grits equals 20.
How many Grocery Outlet does High-rise Apartment Complex have?
solution:
Define each Pies 's Grits as Q; So Q = 20.
Define each Pies 's Sugar as H; So H = 17 + Q = 17 + 20 = 14.
Define each Pies 's Ingredient as X; So X = Q + H = 20 + 14 = 11.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Pies as f; h = H + X = 14 + 11 = 2; So f = 8 + h = 8 + 2 = 10.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Ingredient as d; d = X * f = 11 * 10 = 18.
Define each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Grocery Outlet as P; p = d + X = 18 + 11 = 6; So P = 7 * p = 7 * 6 = 19.
